<div id="what-is-bluesky"></div>
<h2>What is Bluesky?</h2>
<p><a href="https://bsky.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bluesky</a> is a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/11/most-popular-social-media-platforms">social media platform</a> that allows users to post short copy posts, images, and videos. While videos and images are prevalent, Bluesky is similar to X in that the platform features more text-based posts. While the character limit is 350 per post, Bluesky allows users to group longer content in threads.</p>
<p>This similarity to X is by design. Bluesky originally launched back in <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2019/12/11/twitter-ceo-jack-dorsey-announces-bluesky-social-media-standards-push.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2019</a> as a research project at X that was focused on exploring decentralized social media. It became its own independent company in 2021 when Jack Dorsey left then Twitter.</p>
<p>The platform grew by invitation only in 2023 before finally becoming open to all users (over 13 years of age) in early 2024. (Itâ€™s worth noting that <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/article/2024/may/07/jack-dorsey-quits-bluesky-board-urges-users-stay-elon-musk-x-twitter" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Jack Dorsey left Bluesky in 2024</a>, too, but this has more to do with the platformâ€™s founding story than its use in your marketing strategy.)</p>
<p>When it comes to your<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/01/07/best-marketing-strategies"> marketing strategy</a>, Bluesky will likely look familiar to other social media platforms. In terms of layout and platform experience, itâ€™s very similar to X. The left-hand menu, the dual-option Discover and Following feeds, and the publish button are a lot like its competitor platform if not exactly the same.</p>
<p>If youâ€™ve been active on X, youâ€™ll be able to navigate the Bluesky platform easily.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-30-million-followers-png.avif" alt="Bluesky for marketing - post from Bluesky." width="936" height="457" class="aligncenter wp-image-90691 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-30-million-followers-png.avif 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-30-million-followers-300x146.avif 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-30-million-followers-768x375.avif 768w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-30-million-followers-480x234.avif 480w" sizes="(max-width: 936px) 100vw, 936px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Looking nice and familiar, Bluesky.</em></p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="ðŸ›‘" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><strong> Need more social media ideas?</strong> Download <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/social-media-calendar-template?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Template_MonthlySocialMediaCalendar_Download">Your Copy &amp; Paste Social Media Calendar</a></p>
<div id="how-is-bluesky-different"></div>
<h2>How is Bluesky different from other social media platforms?</h2>
<p>As an X competitor, Bluesky is similar to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/07/26/instagram-threads">Instagram Threads</a> and Mastodon. These platforms use the same approach to short-form posts that enable conversations with other platform users.</p>
<p>Here are a few key ways that Bluesky is different.</p>
<h3>Decentralized</h3>
<p>Bluesky is decentralized. This means that it runs on an open AT protocol, which isnâ€™t controlled by a single organization.</p>
<p>Because there isnâ€™t centralized control, users have more control over their data and, importantly, their app experience. There is not a single, central instance of the Bluesky platform. Users can customize and build feeds to tailor their experience on the app to their interests.</p>
<p>In fact, there are more than <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/jay.bsky.team/post/3lbd2ee2pwd2r" target="_blank" rel="noopener">50,000</a> algorithmic feeds that users can opt into.</p>
<h3>Data control<strong>Â </strong></h3>
<p>Even though this is a result of the decentralized platform, data control is worth calling out specifically. Bluesky gives users more control over where their data is stored or not stored, unlike competitors like Threads, which is connected and controlled by Meta.</p>
<p>This control means more user privacy, but it also means less insight into analytics on the platform.</p>
<h3>Community</h3>
<p>Other platform algorithms prioritized the network effect with an algorithm serving content and profiles. Bluesky allows users more control over the feed and the content they consume on the platform, so the focus is on creating many communities of users tied together by common interests and, in turn, common content.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-discover-png.avif" alt="Bluesky for marketing - discover page." width="510" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-90692 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-discover-png.avif 510w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-discover-255x300.avif 255w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-discover-480x565.avif 480w" sizes="(max-width: 510px) 100vw, 510px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Instead of serving a single algorithm-driven feed, Bluesky allows users to subscribe to multiple feeds and curate their experience on the platform.</em></p>
<h3>Ads</h3>
<p>Hereâ€™s where Bluesky really diverges from its closest competitors. For now, the platform is completely ad-free. Thatâ€™s important to note for your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/stretch-your-marketing-budget">marketing budget</a> and strategy. So, while you wonâ€™t put dollars directly into <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/01/12/how-to-generate-leads">getting leads</a> on Bluesky, you may need to invest more time in doing so since there are no <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/ppc">paid ad</a> shortcuts.</p>
<div id="how-popular-is-bluesky"></div>
<h2>How popular is Bluesky?</h2>
<p>Bluesky has <a href="https://www.cnet.com/tech/how-and-why-to-join-bluesky-which-now-has-30-million-users-as-a-twitter-alternative/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">30 million</a> users. Now, this might sound dismissable when you consider the fact that X has <a href="https://backlinko.com/twitter-users" target="_blank" rel="noopener">360 million</a> users and <a href="https://explodingtopics.com/blog/threads-users" target="_blank" rel="noopener">320 million</a> people use Instagram Threads. Each of those is dwarfed by LinkedInâ€”another platform thatâ€™s a little more text-focusedâ€”and has <a href="https://about.linkedin.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">1 billion users</a> worldwide.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-milestone-png.avif" alt="Bluesky for marketing - post from Bluesky about growth milestone." width="936" height="237" class="aligncenter wp-image-90693 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-milestone-png.avif 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-milestone-300x76.avif 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-milestone-768x194.avif 768w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-milestone-480x122.avif 480w" sizes="(max-width: 936px) 100vw, 936px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://bsky.app/profile/bsky.app/post/3lh5iyaqqos24" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></p>
<p>But itâ€™s important to call out how quickly Blueskyâ€™s user base is growing. The total audience on the platform more than doubled between October and December last year.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-statista-png.avif" alt="Bluesky for marketing - bar graph from Statista." width="789" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-90694 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-statista-png.avif 789w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-statista-300x228.avif 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-statista-768x584.avif 768w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/bluesky-marketing-wordstream-statista-480x365.avif 480w" sizes="(max-width: 789px) 100vw, 789px" /></p>
